Description: Lip sherd of Milesian Fikellura pottery trefoil oinochoe with part of neck; white slip; interior: streaky black on upper right edge of sherd; exterior: lip black, flaking off; moulded ridge at junction with neck decorated with band of painted dot and billet pattern.
Curator's comments: Sherd joins British Museum 1886,0401.1051 and probably belongs to same pot as British Museum 1924,1201.921.
Bibliographic references: CVA British Museum 8 / Corpus Vasorum Antiquorum: Great Britain 13, British Museum 8 (9, no. 2)
Möller 2000 / Naukratis, Trade in Archaic Greece (p. 248, no. 6)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GF.160)
